# Documented Onboarding Load score

Use this when adding, changing, or explaining onboarding scores in Developer Journey Atlas.

## Agent prompt (copyable)

```
Design and maintain the Atlas Documented Onboarding Load score.

Goal: for any platform, show (1) where it sits overall and (2) where it sits among peers.

Rules:
- Score = documented load to first success on the selected route. Not UX, drop-off, time, or conversion.
- Higher score = heavier documented load (harder path), not "worse product".
- Never publish ordinal rankings (#3 easiest) or leaderboards.
- ranking_allowed stays false on heuristic artifacts.
- Peer math only against same first_success_type (finish line). Different finish lines are not comparable.
- Overall peer set: corpus ∩ same finish line ∩ not not-comparable.
- Category peer set: category ∩ same finish line ∩ not not-comparable.
- Require at least 3 peers; otherwise mark placement unavailable.
- Underlying meter: existing heuristic_effort_score (actions + weighted friction gates).
- Public score: percentile of effort within the peer set (0 = lightest, 100 = heaviest).
- Bands: Light 0–24, Moderate 25–74, Heavy 75–100.
- Always show inspectable breakdown: effort, required actions, gates, waits.
- Version the model (onboarding-load-1.0). Bump when weights or peer rules change.
- Do not invent payment/install requirements; only use documented quality/friction fields.
```

## Locked decisions

| Decision | Choice |
|---|---|
| Name | Documented Onboarding Load |
| Direction | Higher = heavier load |
| Overall peers | Same `first_success_type` across corpus |
| Category peers | Same category ∩ same `first_success_type` |
| Meter | `heuristic_effort_score` from selected-path-heuristic |
| Public number | Percentile 0–100 within peer set |
| Bands | Light / Moderate / Heavy |
| Min peers | 3 |
| Rankings | Forbidden |

## Implementation home

- Core: `packages/journey-corpus/src/core/onboardingScore.ts`
- Exposed on journey payload as `onboardingScore`
- UI: journey card shows overall + peer placements with breakdown
- Tests: `packages/journey-corpus/tests/app/onboardingScore.test.mjs`

## Honesty copy (required)

Always pair the score with language like:

> Documentation-derived route load only. Not observed time, drop-off, or usability.
